=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Guides_Multichannel-Expansion_ex4 ===

DESCRIPTION: A dark pure_tone sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 133 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and percussive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally sparse.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: dark
  crest_factor_db: percussive
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: sparse
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 132.7152
  harmonic_decay_rate: -7.0870
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5217
  pitch_clarity: 28.6225
  inharmonicity: 0.4773
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -19.0732
  resonance_freq: 236.8652

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Multichannel Expansion Example 4
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Guides/Multichannel-Expansion.html
// Tags: Multichannel-Expansion, Guides
// ---
// --- Example 4 ---
{ RLPF.ar(Saw.ar([100,250],0.05), XLine.kr(8000,400,5), 0.05) }.play;

// the [100,250] array of frequency inputs to Saw causes Saw.ar to return
// an array of two Saws, that array causes RLPF.ar to create two RLPFs.
// Both RLPFs share a single instance of XLine.
